sentences: Sam Teskey (born 1989) is an Australian blues musician, best known for his work with the Teskey Brothers.
Sam won the ARIA Award for Engineer of the Year in 2019.
His debut studio album, Cycles, was released on 8 October 2021 via Ivy League Records.
Sam Teskey was born in 1989 at his parents home in Warrandyte, Victoria, in the room above what is now their studio.
He was close to his brother Josh, with Josh saying in 2021, "We had these bird calls we'd do so we could always find each other in bush near where we lived.
